* [A003106](https://oeis.org/A003106) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3106)): Number of partitions of n into parts 5k+2 or 5k+3.
* [A003107](https://oeis.org/A003107) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3107)): Number of partitions of n into Fibonacci parts (with a single type of 1).
* [A003108](https://oeis.org/A003108) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3108)): Number of partitions of n into cubes.
* [A003114](https://oeis.org/A003114) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3114)): Number of partitions of n into parts 5k+1 or 5k+4.
* [A003115](https://oeis.org/A003115) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3115)): a(n) = 4^floor(n/2)\*a(n-1) - a(n-2), for n >= 2, with a(0) = a(1) = 1.
* [A003124](https://oeis.org/A003124) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3124)): One of the basic cycles in the x->3x-1 (x odd) or x/2 (x even) problem.
* [A003128](https://oeis.org/A003128) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3128)): Number of driving-point impedances of an n-terminal network.
* [A003132](https://oeis.org/A003132) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3132)): Sum of squares of digits of n.
* [A003136](https://oeis.org/A003136) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3136)): Loeschian numbers: numbers of the form x^2 + xy + y^2; norms of vectors in A2 lattice.
* [A003138](https://oeis.org/A003138) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3138)): Nearest integer to 24\*(2^n - 1)/n.
* [A003141](https://oeis.org/A003141) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3141)): Minimal number of arcs whose reversal yields a transitive tournament.
* [A003143](https://oeis.org/A003143) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3143)): a(2\*n) = floor( 17\*2^n/14 ), a(2\*n+1) = floor( 12\*2^n/7 ).
* [A003144](https://oeis.org/A003144) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3144)): Positions of letter a in the tribonacci word abacabaabacababac... generated by a->ab, b->ac, c->a (cf. A092782).
* [A003145](https://oeis.org/A003145) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3145)): Positions of letter b in the tribonacci word abacabaabacababac... generated by a->ab, b->ac, c->a (cf. A092782).
* [A003146](https://oeis.org/A003146) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3146)): Positions of letter c in the tribonacci word abacabaabacababac... generated by a->ab, b->ac, c->a (cf. A092782).
* [A003148](https://oeis.org/A003148) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3148)): a(n+1) = a(n) + 2n\*(2n+1)\*a(n-1), with a(0) = a(1) = 1.
* [A003149](https://oeis.org/A003149) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3149)): a(n) = Sum\_\{k=0..n\} k!(n-k)!.
* [A003151](https://oeis.org/A003151) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3151)): Beatty sequence for 1+sqrt(2); a(n) = floor(n\*(1+sqrt(2))).
* [A003152](https://oeis.org/A003152) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3152)): A Beatty sequence: a(n) = floor(n\*(1+1/sqrt(2))).
* [A003153](https://oeis.org/A003153) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3153)): a(n) = integer nearest n\*(1+sqrt(2)).
* [A003154](https://oeis.org/A003154) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3154)): Centered 12-gonal numbers. Also star numbers: 6\*n\*(n-1) + 1.
* [A003156](https://oeis.org/A003156) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3156)): A self-generating sequence (see Comments for definition).
* [A003157](https://oeis.org/A003157) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3157)): A self-generating sequence (see Comments in A003156 for the definition).
* [A003158](https://oeis.org/A003158) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3158)): A self-generating sequence (see Comments in A003156 for the definition).
* [A003159](https://oeis.org/A003159) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3159)): Numbers n whose binary representation ends in an even number of zeros.
* [A003160](https://oeis.org/A003160) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3160)): a(1) = a(2) = 1, a(n) = n - a(a(n-1)) - a(a(n-2)).
* [A003161](https://oeis.org/A003161) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3161)): A binomial coefficient sum.
* [A003165](https://oeis.org/A003165) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3165)): a(n) = floor(n/2) + 1 - d(n), where d(n) is the number of divisors of n.
* [A003168](https://oeis.org/A003168) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3168)): Number of blobs with 2n+1 edges.
* [A003169](https://oeis.org/A003169) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3169)): Number of 2-line arrays; or number of P-graphs with 2n edges.
* [A003176](https://oeis.org/A003176) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3176)): Integer part of 24(2^n-1)/n.
* [A003177](https://oeis.org/A003177) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3177)): a(n) = ceiling(24(2^n-1)/n).
* [A003185](https://oeis.org/A003185) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3185)): a(n) = (4\*n+1)(4\*n+5).
* [A003188](https://oeis.org/A003188) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3188)): Decimal equivalent of Gray code for n.
* [A003215](https://oeis.org/A003215) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3215)): Hex (or centered hexagonal) numbers: 3\*n\*(n+1)+1 (crystal ball sequence for hexagonal lattice).
* [A003221](https://oeis.org/A003221) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3221)): Number of even permutations of length n with no fixed points.
* [A003222](https://oeis.org/A003222) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3222)): a(n) = 2^(3\*n+1) - 2\*n\*(2\*n+1).
* [A003229](https://oeis.org/A003229) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3229)): a(n) = a(n-1) + 2\*a(n-3) with a(0)=a(1)=1, a(2)=3.
* [A003230](https://oeis.org/A003230) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3230)): Expansion of 1/((1-x)\*(1-2\*x)\*(1-x-2\*x^3)).
* [A003231](https://oeis.org/A003231) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3231)): a(n) = floor(n\*(sqrt(5)+5)/2).
* [A003232](https://oeis.org/A003232) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3232)): Expansion of (x-1)\*(x^2-4\*x-1)/(1-2\*x)^2.
* [A003233](https://oeis.org/A003233) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3233)): Numbers k such that A003231(A001950(k)) = A001950(A003231(k)).
* [A003234](https://oeis.org/A003234) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3234)): Numbers k such that A003231(A001950(k)) = A001950(A003231(k)) - 1.
* [A003235](https://oeis.org/A003235) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3235)): a(n) = Sum\_\{k=0..n\} (-1)^(n-k) C(n,k)\*C(k^2,n).
* [A003236](https://oeis.org/A003236) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3236)): a(n) = Sum\_\{k=0..n\} (-1)^(n-k) C(n,k)\*C((k+1)^2, n).
* [A003238](https://oeis.org/A003238) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3238)): Number of rooted trees with n vertices in which vertices at the same level have the same degree.
* [A003239](https://oeis.org/A003239) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3239)): Number of rooted planar trees with n non-root nodes: circularly cycling the subtrees at the root gives equivalent trees.
* [A003242](https://oeis.org/A003242) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3242)): Number of compositions of n such that no two adjacent parts are equal (Carlitz compositions).
* [A003249](https://oeis.org/A003249) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3249)): a(n) = A001950(A003234(n)) + 1.
* [A003250](https://oeis.org/A003250) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3250)): The number m such that A001950(m) = A003231(A003234(n)).
* [A003251](https://oeis.org/A003251) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3251)): Complement of A003250.
* [A003252](https://oeis.org/A003252) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3252)): The number m such that A003251(m) = A003231(n).
* [A003253](https://oeis.org/A003253) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3253)): Complement of A003252.
* [A003256](https://oeis.org/A003256) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3256)): a(n) is the number m such that A242094(m) = A001950(n).
* [A003257](https://oeis.org/A003257) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3257)): Complement of A003256.
* [A003258](https://oeis.org/A003258) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3258)): The number m such that c'(m) = A005206(A003231(n)), where c'(m) = A249115(m) is the m-th positive integer not in A003231.
* [A003259](https://oeis.org/A003259) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3259)): Complement of A003258.
* [A003261](https://oeis.org/A003261) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3261)): Woodall (or Riesel) numbers: n\*2^n - 1.
* [A003265](https://oeis.org/A003265) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3265)): Not representable by truncated tribonacci sequence 2, 4, 7, 13, 24, 44, 81, ....
* [A003266](https://oeis.org/A003266) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3266)): Product of first n nonzero Fibonacci numbers F(1), ..., F(n).
* [A003269](https://oeis.org/A003269) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3269)): a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-4) with a(0) = 0, a(1) = a(2) = a(3) = 1.
* [A003270](https://oeis.org/A003270) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3270)): A nonrepetitive sequence.
* [A003274](https://oeis.org/A003274) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3274)): Number of key permutations of length n: permutations \{a\_i\} with \|a\_i-a\_\{i-1\}\| = 1 or 2.
* [A003277](https://oeis.org/A003277) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3277)): Cyclic numbers: k such that k and phi(k) are relatively prime; also k such that there is just one group of order k, i.e., A000001(n) = 1.
* [A003278](https://oeis.org/A003278) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3278)): Szekeres's sequence: a(n)-1 in ternary = n-1 in binary; also: a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2, and thereafter a(n) is smallest number k which avoids any 3-term arithmetic progression in a(1), a(2), ..., a(n-1), k.
* [A003292](https://oeis.org/A003292) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3292)): Number of 4-line partitions of n decreasing across rows.
* [A003308](https://oeis.org/A003308) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3308)): a(n) = 2\*n^(n-2).
* [A003312](https://oeis.org/A003312) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3312)): a(1) = 3; for n>0, a(n+1) = a(n) + floor((a(n)-1)/2).
* [A003314](https://oeis.org/A003314) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3314)): Binary entropy function: a(1)=0; for n > 1, a(n) = n + min \{ a(k)+a(n-k) : 1 <= k <= n-1 \}.
* [A003318](https://oeis.org/A003318) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3318)): a(n + 1) = 1 + a( floor(n/1) ) + a( floor(n/2) ) + ... + a( floor(n/n) ).
* [A003319](https://oeis.org/A003319) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3319)): Number of connected permutations of [1..n] (those not fixing [1..j] for 0 < j < n). Also called indecomposable permutations, or irreducible permutations.
* [A003320](https://oeis.org/A003320) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3320)): a(n) = max\_\{k=0..n\} k^(n-k).
* [A003324](https://oeis.org/A003324) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3324)): A nonrepetitive sequence.
* [A003325](https://oeis.org/A003325) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3325)): Numbers that are the sum of 2 positive cubes.
* [A003402](https://oeis.org/A003402) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3402)): G.f.: 1/((1-x)\*(1-x^2)\*(1-x^3)^2\*(1-x^4)\*(1-x^5)).
* [A003408](https://oeis.org/A003408) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3408)): a(n) = binomial(3n+6, n).
* [A003409](https://oeis.org/A003409) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3409)): a(n) = 3\*binomial(2n-1,n).
* [A003410](https://oeis.org/A003410) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3410)): Expansion of (1+x)(1+x^2)/(1-x-x^3).
* [A003411](https://oeis.org/A003411) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3411)): Losing initial positions in game: two players alternate in removing >= 1 stones; last player wins; first player may not remove all stones; each move <= 3 times previous move.
* [A003413](https://oeis.org/A003413) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3413)): From a nim-like game.
* [A003415](https://oeis.org/A003415) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3415)): a(n) = n' = arithmetic derivative of n: a(0) = a(1) = 0, a(prime) = 1, a(mn) = m\*a(n) + n\*a(m).
* [A003417](https://oeis.org/A003417) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3417)): Continued fraction for e.
* [A003418](https://oeis.org/A003418) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3418)): Least common multiple (or LCM) of \{1, 2, ..., n\} for n >= 1, a(0) = 1.
* [A003422](https://oeis.org/A003422) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3422)): Left factorials: !n = Sum\_\{k=0..n-1\} k!.
* [A003434](https://oeis.org/A003434) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3434)): Number of iterations of phi(x) at n needed to reach 1.
* [A003435](https://oeis.org/A003435) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3435)): Number of directed Hamiltonian circuits on n-octahedron with a marked starting node.
* [A003436](https://oeis.org/A003436) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3436)): Number of inequivalent labeled Hamiltonian circuits on n-octahedron. Interlacing chords joining 2n points on circle.
* [A003440](https://oeis.org/A003440) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3440)): Number of binary vectors with restricted repetitions.
* [A003441](https://oeis.org/A003441) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3441)): Number of nonequivalent dissections of a polygon into n triangles by nonintersecting diagonals rooted at a cell up to rotation.
* [A003451](https://oeis.org/A003451) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3451)): Number of nonequivalent dissections of an n-gon into 3 polygons by nonintersecting diagonals up to rotation.
* [A003452](https://oeis.org/A003452) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3452)): Number of nonequivalent dissections of an n-gon into 3 polygons by nonintersecting diagonals rooted at a cell up to rotation and reflection.
* [A003453](https://oeis.org/A003453) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3453)): Number of nonequivalent dissections of an n-gon into 3 polygons by nonintersecting diagonals up to rotation and reflection.
* [A003461](https://oeis.org/A003461) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3461)): Bode numbers multiplied by 10: 4 + 3\*floor(2^(n-1)).
* [A003462](https://oeis.org/A003462) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3462)): a(n) = (3^n - 1)/2.
* [A003463](https://oeis.org/A003463) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3463)): a(n) = (5^n - 1)/4.
* [A003464](https://oeis.org/A003464) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3464)): a(n) = (6^n - 1)/5.
* [A003467](https://oeis.org/A003467) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3467)): Number of minimal covers of an n-set that cover exactly 3 points uniquely.
* [A003468](https://oeis.org/A003468) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3468)): Number of minimal 3-covers of a labeled n-set.
* [A003469](https://oeis.org/A003469) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3469)): Number of minimal covers of an (n + 1)-set by a collection of n nonempty subsets, a(n) = A035348(n,n-1).
* [A003470](https://oeis.org/A003470) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3470)): a(n) = n\*a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 1 + (-1)^n.
* [A003472](https://oeis.org/A003472) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3472)): a(n) = 2^(n-4)\*C(n,4).
* [A003476](https://oeis.org/A003476) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3476)): a(n) = a(n-1) + 2a(n-3).
* [A003477](https://oeis.org/A003477) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3477)): Expansion of 1/((1-2x)(1+x^2)(1-x-2x^3)).
* [A003478](https://oeis.org/A003478) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3478)): Expansion of 1/(1-2x)(1-x-2x^3).
* [A003479](https://oeis.org/A003479) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3479)): Expansion of 1/((1-x)\*(1-x-2\*x^3)).
* [A003480](https://oeis.org/A003480) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3480)): a(n) = 4\*a(n-1) - 2\*a(n-2) (n >= 3).
* [A003481](https://oeis.org/A003481) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3481)): a(n) = 7\*a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 5.
* [A003482](https://oeis.org/A003482) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3482)): a(n) = 7\*a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 4, with a(0) = 0, a(1) = 5.
* [A003484](https://oeis.org/A003484) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3484)): Radon function, also called Hurwitz-Radon numbers.
* [A003485](https://oeis.org/A003485) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3485)): Hurwitz-Radon function at powers of 2.
* [A003486](https://oeis.org/A003486) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3486)): a(n) = (n^2 + 1)\*3^n.
* [A003499](https://oeis.org/A003499) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3499)): a(n) = 6\*a(n-1) - a(n-2), with a(0) = 2, a(1) = 6.
* [A003500](https://oeis.org/A003500) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3500)): a(n) = 4\*a(n-1) - a(n-2) with a(0) = 2, a(1) = 4.
* [A003501](https://oeis.org/A003501) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3501)): a(n) = 5\*a(n-1) - a(n-2), with a(0) = 2, a(1) = 5.
* [A003504](https://oeis.org/A003504) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3504)): a(0)=a(1)=1; thereafter a(n+1) = (1/n)\*Sum\_\{k=0..n\} a(k)^2 (a(n) is not always integral!).
* [A003506](https://oeis.org/A003506) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3506)): Triangle of denominators in Leibniz's Harmonic Triangle a(n,k), n >= 1, 1 <= k <= n.
* [A003508](https://oeis.org/A003508) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3508)): a(1) = 1; for n>1, a(n) = a(n-1) + 1 + sum of distinct prime factors of a(n-1) that are < a(n-1).
* [A003511](https://oeis.org/A003511) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3511)): A Beatty sequence: floor( n \* (1 + sqrt(3))/2 ).
* [A003512](https://oeis.org/A003512) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3512)): A Beatty sequence: floor(n\*(sqrt(3) + 2)).
* [A003516](https://oeis.org/A003516) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3516)): Binomial coefficients C(2n+1, n-2).
* [A003517](https://oeis.org/A003517) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3517)): Number of permutations of [n+1] with exactly 1 increasing subsequence of length 3.
* [A003518](https://oeis.org/A003518) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3518)): a(n) = 8\*binomial(2\*n+1,n-3)/(n+5).
* [A003519](https://oeis.org/A003519) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3519)): a(n) = 10\*C(2n+1, n-4)/(n+6).
* [A003520](https://oeis.org/A003520) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3520)): a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-5); a(0) = ... = a(4) = 1.
* [A003522](https://oeis.org/A003522) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3522)): a(n) = Sum\_\{k=0..n\} C(n-k,3k).
* [A003524](https://oeis.org/A003524) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3524)): Divisors of 2^12 - 1.
* [A003527](https://oeis.org/A003527) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3527)): Divisors of 2^16 - 1.
* [A003539](https://oeis.org/A003539) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3539)): a(n)=3\*a(n-1)+16 (the first 11 terms are primes).
* [A003555](https://oeis.org/A003555) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3555)): Sum\{1,2,...,(10^n - 1)/9\}, or (10^n -1)/9)((10^n -1)/9 +1)/2 (n-th term is the middle 2(n-1) digits of the (n+9)-th term for n > 1).
* [A003557](https://oeis.org/A003557) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3557)): n divided by largest squarefree divisor of n; if n = Product p(k)^e(k) then a(n) = Product p(k)^(e(k)-1), with a(1) = 1.
* [A003558](https://oeis.org/A003558) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3558)): Least number m > 0 such that 2^m == +-1 (mod 2n + 1).
* [A003559](https://oeis.org/A003559) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3559)): Least number m such that 3^m = +- 1 mod 3n + 1.
* [A003560](https://oeis.org/A003560) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3560)): Least number m such that 4^m = +- 1 mod 4n + 1.
* [A003561](https://oeis.org/A003561) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3561)): Least number m such that 5^m = +- 1 mod 5n + 1.
* [A003562](https://oeis.org/A003562) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3562)): Least number m such that 6^m = +- 1 mod 6n + 1.
* [A003564](https://oeis.org/A003564) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3564)): Least number m such that 8^m = +- 1 mod 8n + 1.
* [A003565](https://oeis.org/A003565) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3565)): Least number m such that 9^m = +- 1 mod 9n + 1.
* [A003566](https://oeis.org/A003566) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3566)): Least number m such that 10^m = +- 1 mod 10n + 1.
* [A003568](https://oeis.org/A003568) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3568)): Least number m such that 12^m = +- 1 mod 12n + 1.
* [A003569](https://oeis.org/A003569) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3569)): a(n) = least positive number m such that 4^m == +1 or -1 mod 2n + 1, with a(0) = 0 by convention.
* [A003570](https://oeis.org/A003570) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3570)): a(n) = least positive number m such that 8^m == +1 or -1 mod 2n + 1, with a(0) = 0 by convention.
* [A003571](https://oeis.org/A003571) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3571)): Order of 3 mod 3n+1.
* [A003572](https://oeis.org/A003572) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3572)): Order of 3 mod 3n+2.
* [A003573](https://oeis.org/A003573) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3573)): Order of 4 mod 4n+1.
* [A003574](https://oeis.org/A003574) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3574)): Order of 4 mod 4n-1.
* [A003575](https://oeis.org/A003575) ([program](/edit/?oeis=3575)): Dowling numbers: e.g.f.: exp(x + (exp(b\*x) - 1)/b) with b=3.

* [A022822](https://oeis.org/A022822) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22822)): a(n) = [ (n+2)/(n-1) ] + [ (n+4)/(n-2) ] + ... + [ (3n-2)/1 ].

* [A022825](https://oeis.org/A022825) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22825)): a(n) = a([ n/2 ]) + a([ n/3 ]) + . . . + a([ n/n ]) for n > 1, a(1) = 1.
* [A022826](https://oeis.org/A022826) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22826)): a(n) = a([ (n+1)/2 ]) + a([ (n+1)/3 ]) + . . . + a([ (n+1)/n ]).
* [A022831](https://oeis.org/A022831) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22831)): a(n) = c(1)p(1) + ... + c(n)p(n), where c(i) = 1 if a(i-1) <= p(i) and c(i) = -1 if a(i-1) > p(i), for i = 1,...,n (p(i) = primes).
* [A022833](https://oeis.org/A022833) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22833)): a(0)=2; thereafter a(n) = a(n-1) + prime(n) if a(n-1) < prime(n), otherwise a(n) = a(n-1) - prime(n). Cf. A008348.
* [A022834](https://oeis.org/A022834) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22834)): a(n) = c(1)p(3) + ... + c(n)p(n+2), where c(i) = 1 if a(i-1) <= p(i+2) and c(i) = -1 if a(i-1) > p(i+2) (p(i) = primes).
* [A022835](https://oeis.org/A022835) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22835)): a(n) = c(1)p(3) + ... + c(n)p(n+2), where c(i) = 1 if a(i-1) < p(i+2) and c(i) = -1 if a(i-1) >= p(i+2) (p(i) = primes).
* [A022836](https://oeis.org/A022836) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22836)): a(n) = c(1)\*p(0) + ... + c(n)\*p(n-1), where c(i) = 1 if a(i-1) <= p(i-1) and c(i) = -1 if a(i-1) > p(i-1) (with p(0) = 1 and p(i) a prime for i >= 1).
* [A022837](https://oeis.org/A022837) ([program](/edit/?oeis=22837)): a(n) = c(0)\*p(0) + ... + c(n)\*p(n), where c(i) = 1 if a(i-1) < p(i) and c(i) = -1 if a(i-1) >= p(i) (p(0) = 1, p(i) = prime(i)).
